WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:12.250 --> 00:00:14.583
<i>There are many
different kinds of days here.</i>

3
00:00:14.666 --> 00:00:16.791
<i>Good days. bad days.</i>

4
00:00:17.875 --> 00:00:20.041
<i>But there really aren't many days
like today.</i>

5
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:23.125
So I had to be sure.

6
00:00:24.166 --> 00:00:28.416
We did those extra tests
and sure enough. your endoscopy...

7
00:00:29.458 --> 00:00:32.416
Well. there's still some polyps
and lesions in your small intestine.

8
00:00:33.750 --> 00:00:36.125
but less than when you got here.

9
00:00:37.291 --> 00:00:38.958
Which means you're healing.

10
00:00:39.875 --> 00:00:43.250
Which means the terminal diagnosis
was an error.

11
00:00:45.541 --> 00:00:46.666
Which means...

12
00:00:48.041 --> 00:00:49.250
you're going home.

13
00:00:55.916 --> 00:00:56.916
Wait.

14
00:00:57.583 --> 00:01:00.375
I have peripheral T-cell lymphoma.

15
00:01:01.875 --> 00:01:04.458
I saw the polyps on my first endoscopy.

16
00:01:04.541 --> 00:01:07.500
and after all the chemo.
the polyps were worse.

17
00:01:09.833 --> 00:01:11.625
And they said I'm dying.

18
00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:16.250
When you first got here. it took a while
for the effects of the chemo to wear off.

19
00:01:16.333 --> 00:01:18.500
But now we can see your body is healing.

20
00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:21.875
But I'm not dying?

21
00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:25.333
We're all dying. Sandra.

22
00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:28.458
Each and every one of us.

23
00:01:31.875 --> 00:01:34.375
But right now. for you.

24
00:01:35.416 --> 00:01:38.750
you do not have terminal lymphoma.

25
00:01:40.750 --> 00:01:42.000
I'm sorry.

26
00:01:42.958 --> 00:01:46.375
I have no idea
why I feel the way I feel right now.

27
00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.000
However you feel is correct.

28
00:01:50.833 --> 00:01:53.625
However you're feeling.
whatever it is. is right.

29
00:01:54.458 --> 00:01:56.833
But this is wonderful news. Sandra.

30
00:01:58.208 --> 00:01:59.541
How am I gonna tell them?

31
00:02:00.458 --> 00:02:01.750
Jesus...

32
00:02:03.166 --> 00:02:05.000
Wh-what am I gonna say?

33
00:02:31.166 --> 00:02:32.166
There you are.

34
00:02:37.375 --> 00:02:38.375
Morning.

35
00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:42.416
How did I get here?

36
00:02:43.166 --> 00:02:46.000
You were out of it. so I brought you here.

37
00:02:49.916 --> 00:02:52.166
Okay. I have found myself
down there before.

38
00:02:53.708 --> 00:02:55.083
More than a few times.

39
00:02:56.375 --> 00:02:58.083
Ever since we found it. I...

40
00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.750
Most nights. actually.
I wake up down there.

41
00:03:02.583 --> 00:03:04.625
I sneak back to my room.
try not to wake up Spence.

42
00:03:04.708 --> 00:03:06.541
It's... it's freaky. all right?

43
00:03:08.875 --> 00:03:11.083
I've even woken up in that bed down there.

44
00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:14.958
And the smell of it is just...

45
00:03:16.041 --> 00:03:17.458
It's crazy.

46
00:03:17.541 --> 00:03:20.500
The dreams. sleepwalking.

47
00:03:21.708 --> 00:03:22.708
Got to be my meds.

48
00:03:22.750 --> 00:03:26.250
Our meds don't make the halls
look different.

49
00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:31.041
Our meds don't make me see people
in the hallways.

50
00:03:31.125 --> 00:03:32.791
in the room. in the goddamn mirror.

51
00:03:33.458 --> 00:03:35.750
I think you know
what I'm talking about. Kevin.

52
00:03:37.541 --> 00:03:38.708
So. please.

53
00:03:39.666 --> 00:03:42.375
If you do. don't make me go
another minute feeling crazy.

54
00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.000
Yeah.

55
00:03:47.666 --> 00:03:49.041
Okay. I do.

56
00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:53.541
Sometimes the rooms change.

57
00:03:54.666 --> 00:03:56.083
And the walls change.

58
00:03:57.083 --> 00:03:59.875
And sometimes you'll hear a noise
and you'll turn around.

59
00:04:01.458 --> 00:04:03.083
And you're not alone.

60
00:04:04.250 --> 00:04:06.750
And there'll be somebody
coming towards you

61
00:04:06.833 --> 00:04:11.208
from out of the dark or the firelight.

62
00:04:11.291 --> 00:04:14.458
and you'll look up
and you'll see this old...

63
00:04:14.541 --> 00:04:15.583
Woman?

64
00:04:16.916 --> 00:04:17.916
Man.

65
00:04:19.208 --> 00:04:22.500
Old man. He's got gray hair.

66
00:04:22.583 --> 00:04:23.875
Yeah. I've seen him before.

67
00:04:26.666 --> 00:04:28.000
But mostly. I see her.

68
00:04:29.375 --> 00:04:30.375
An old woman.

69
00:04:31.583 --> 00:04:33.083
And she's got these. like...

70
00:04:35.166 --> 00:04:36.333
milky eyes.

71
00:04:39.166 --> 00:04:40.333
You ever see her?

72
00:04:41.750 --> 00:04:43.833
Not as much as I see him. but...

73
00:04:45.333 --> 00:04:46.500
glimpses.

74
00:04:47.625 --> 00:04:48.625
Yeah.

75
00:04:50.875 --> 00:04:52.458
Let's get everyone to the library.

76
00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:55.541
- Oh. my god. What?
- Get dressed.

77
00:04:56.125 --> 00:04:57.541
Emergency meeting. Library.

78
00:04:57.625 --> 00:04:58.875
Is everything okay?

79
00:05:03.791 --> 00:05:05.083
Is. um...

80
00:05:06.083 --> 00:05:07.500
Is everything okay. Ilonka?

81
00:05:08.041 --> 00:05:11.291
Uh. yeah. Yeah. everything's...

82
00:05:11.875 --> 00:05:13.583
- okay.
- Oh. God.

83
00:05:19.666 --> 00:05:22.166
Oh. gosh.

84
00:05:25.875 --> 00:05:27.125
Oh. it's unlocked again.

85
00:05:28.333 --> 00:05:29.833
Bet she locks it again tonight.

86
00:05:31.791 --> 00:05:33.666
- You okay. Sandra?
- I'm fine.

87
00:05:34.833 --> 00:05:36.333
What's all this about?

88
00:05:36.416 --> 00:05:39.541
Yeah. I'm sorry. but I don't know
what the fuck you guys are talking about.

89
00:05:39.625 --> 00:05:41.458
Seriously. No bullshit.

90
00:05:41.541 --> 00:05:44.875
Anyone else seeing changing hallways
or old-ass ghost?

91
00:05:44.958 --> 00:05:46.000
Hmm. Negative.

92
00:05:46.083 --> 00:05:48.166
I'm sorry. No. nothing like that.

93
00:05:48.250 --> 00:05:51.666
Me neither. And I'd totally lie about it
if I thought it was funny.

94
00:05:51.750 --> 00:05:53.000
but it's not funny. right?

95
00:05:53.083 --> 00:05:54.083
For real?

96
00:05:54.125 --> 00:05:57.083
Like the old hallways
with the flowers and the lanterns.

97
00:05:57.166 --> 00:05:59.083
and the old man and the woman?

98
00:05:59.166 --> 00:06:01.000
She's got. uh. milky eyes.

99
00:06:01.083 --> 00:06:02.958
- Yeah. cataracts.
- Cataracts.

100
00:06:03.041 --> 00:06:07.291
And... and she keeps talking about
how she's hungry. she's starving.

101
00:06:07.875 --> 00:06:08.875
No.

102
00:06:09.291 --> 00:06:11.791
I haven't seen anything.
like. any of that.

103
00:06:11.875 --> 00:06:13.583
That doesn't make any sense.

104
00:06:13.666 --> 00:06:18.750
I mean. if we did see ghosts
or whatever. that's great. right?

105
00:06:18.833 --> 00:06:20.750
Isn't that what we were waiting for?
A sign?

106
00:06:20.833 --> 00:06:22.750
Yeah. but it doesn't make any sense.

107
00:06:22.833 --> 00:06:25.583
Like you said.
in a place where so many young people die

108
00:06:25.666 --> 00:06:28.250
before their time
with unfinished business.

109
00:06:28.333 --> 00:06:31.875
the only ghosts you see
are two. like. old people.

110
00:06:32.666 --> 00:06:34.041
We... we both saw it.

111
00:06:34.125 --> 00:06:36.142
- I mean. we both...
- There's a French word for that.

112
00:06:36.166 --> 00:06:39.416
When two people are close.
they share the same...

113
00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:44.166
Yeah. uh. <i>folie à deux.</i>
It means. um. delusion shared by two.

114
00:06:44.750 --> 00:06:45.767
You speak French?

115
00:06:45.791 --> 00:06:48.583
No. but it was the. uh. title
of an <i>X-Files</i> episode...

116
00:06:48.666 --> 00:06:50.333
...and it was awesome.

117
00:06:50.416 --> 00:06:53.041
So none of you guys have seen this?

118
00:06:53.958 --> 00:06:56.583
Any of it? We're... we're both just crazy?

119
00:06:58.625 --> 00:07:00.583
- Maybe it's not...
- Not what?

120
00:07:00.666 --> 00:07:03.541
- Crazy?
- Maybe it's not ghost.

121
00:07:04.875 --> 00:07:08.375
My mom told a story.
something her grandmother told her.

122
00:07:09.583 --> 00:07:11.958
This bedtime story about this thing. uh...

123
00:07:12.708 --> 00:07:14.041
<i>Toshi no Taberu Hito.</i>

124
00:07:14.666 --> 00:07:19.375
It means "eater of years"
or "the years eater."

125
00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:21.875
It looked like an old woman.

126
00:07:21.958 --> 00:07:26.291
And you'd find it in places
where people were going to die.

127
00:07:26.375 --> 00:07:28.250
and eat the years they would have had.

128
00:07:29.666 --> 00:07:33.916
Wait. this was a bedtime story
that your mom told you casually?

129
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.791
No. It was a way for her to process.

130
00:07:37.750 --> 00:07:39.875
She only told me after my dad died.

131
00:07:40.583 --> 00:07:44.166
But if this thing really exists.

132
00:07:44.666 --> 00:07:46.541
I bet it would love a place like this.

133
00:07:48.458 --> 00:07:50.250
We all should have so many years left.

134
00:07:51.458 --> 00:07:53.083
This place would be a feast.

135
00:07:53.666 --> 00:07:56.541
Kevin and Ilonka can also be wrong.

136
00:07:56.625 --> 00:08:00.291
Have fever dreams. overdo their meds
and see shit that isn't there.

137
00:08:00.375 --> 00:08:02.175
Especially when they tell
each other about it.

138
00:08:03.458 --> 00:08:05.583
Let's not forget
the other part of the pact.

139
00:08:05.666 --> 00:08:07.625
We look for signs. but we keep our cool.

140
00:08:08.750 --> 00:08:09.875
Proof.

141
00:08:09.958 --> 00:08:11.718
That's the whole point
of the pact. isn't it?

142
00:08:11.750 --> 00:08:14.666
No. There's more happening here.

143
00:08:17.375 --> 00:08:21.875
I've got to tell you guys something.
but I promised I wouldn't say anything.

144
00:08:22.458 --> 00:08:24.375
You want proof
that there's more going on here?

145
00:08:24.458 --> 00:08:25.458
Well. I got that.

146
00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:29.000
The ritual worked.

147
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:31.083
Stanton admitted it.

148
00:08:32.833 --> 00:08:34.250
One of us is cured.

149
00:08:35.458 --> 00:08:36.958
One of us is going home.

150
00:08:39.166 --> 00:08:40.250
In fact. I think...

151
00:08:41.625 --> 00:08:42.750
And I'm sorry.

152
00:08:44.041 --> 00:08:46.166
But I... I think it's me.

153
00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:47.833
And it can work for you guys too.

154
00:08:47.916 --> 00:08:50.041
But we really have to believe
and do it just right.

155
00:08:50.125 --> 00:08:52.226
- Wait. You're saying you're healed?
- What the fuck. Ilonka?

156
00:08:52.250 --> 00:08:53.625
Hang on. guys.

157
00:08:53.708 --> 00:08:54.833
I think so.

158
00:08:54.916 --> 00:08:56.291
I... I feel it.

159
00:08:56.375 --> 00:08:59.416
No. I... I know the ritual worked.
and we have to do it again.

160
00:08:59.500 --> 00:09:01.458
This is... This isn't funny.

161
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.208
No. she's right. Someone's going home.

162
00:09:04.250 --> 00:09:05.291
Stanton said so.

163
00:09:05.958 --> 00:09:08.250
What the fuck do you mean
someone's going home?

164
00:09:11.083 --> 00:09:12.125
It's me.

165
00:09:15.333 --> 00:09:17.041
Sandra. look.

166
00:09:18.291 --> 00:09:20.041
We all want it to be us.

167
00:09:21.333 --> 00:09:25.333
And that's the thing. It can be all of us.
but we have to really believe...

168
00:09:25.416 --> 00:09:26.958
No. it's actually me.

169
00:09:27.625 --> 00:09:30.333
I'm going home tomorrow.
My grandparents are already on their way.

170
00:09:30.416 --> 00:09:32.958
And it wasn't the ritual.
It was a misdiagnosis.

171
00:09:33.666 --> 00:09:37.500
I had an endoscopy the week before
we even did the stupid ritual

172
00:09:37.583 --> 00:09:40.250
and I was misdiagnosed at the start.

173
00:09:40.333 --> 00:09:43.416
I've got some other GI thing
and so I got to go.

174
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:45.083
and I got to start all over.

175
00:09:45.166 --> 00:09:49.041
The tests. and the trials.
and the treatments. and the whole thing.

176
00:09:49.666 --> 00:09:50.958
I'm sorry. but no.

177
00:09:51.625 --> 00:09:52.833
The ritual didn't work.

178
00:09:54.041 --> 00:09:55.166
No.

179
00:09:55.250 --> 00:09:57.500
Maybe it just worked different.

180
00:09:58.125 --> 00:09:59.583
It's not just that. It... it...

181
00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:01.666
There are signs.
We've had signs. We've had...

182
00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:04.833
And Spence heard that voice
on the intercom after Tristan.

183
00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:08.500
They're pointing at us.
They're guiding us to do the ritual.

184
00:10:08.583 --> 00:10:09.583
That was me too.

185
00:10:11.500 --> 00:10:12.666
I'm so sorry.

186
00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:17.250
That was me on the intercom.
You were talking about... losing faith.

187
00:10:17.333 --> 00:10:19.392
<i>and I thought. just a little nudge.
nothing... nothing too bad.</i>

188
00:10:19.416 --> 00:10:21.833
<i>Just enough to... to give you some hope.</i>

189
00:10:21.916 --> 00:10:23.250
<i>God would want me to.</i>

190
00:10:23.333 --> 00:10:24.333
Hello?

191
00:10:27.458 --> 00:10:28.750
Spence.

192
00:10:29.458 --> 00:10:30.500
<i>Listen.</i>

193
00:10:31.833 --> 00:10:33.976
- Someone's in the recovery room.
- What?

194
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:36.000
Someone's in there
and the door is locked.

195
00:10:36.041 --> 00:10:38.241
- Doors are never locked.
- It's locked.

196
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:40.083
Oh. my god.

197
00:10:42.125 --> 00:10:44.625
I know it was wrong.
and I know it was so stupid.

198
00:10:44.708 --> 00:10:46.083
And I'm so. so sorry.

199
00:10:48.583 --> 00:10:52.916
I'm... I'm a mess right now.
and I'm so... so relieved.

200
00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:54.791
and I'm so ashamed. and...

201
00:10:55.916 --> 00:10:59.416
I don't want to go anywhere.
but I can't wait to go.

202
00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:00.916
And I just...

203
00:11:02.250 --> 00:11:03.250
I feel awful.

204
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:30.250
Ilonka! Hey.

205
00:11:31.500 --> 00:11:32.833
Hey. Katherine.

206
00:11:33.458 --> 00:11:36.833
I know family day isn't until tomorrow.
but I just couldn't wait.

207
00:11:36.916 --> 00:11:38.250
You have to see these.

208
00:11:38.333 --> 00:11:39.958
I'm actually in a hurry.

209
00:11:40.041 --> 00:11:41.708
Oh. no. no. no. It'll just take a second.

210
00:11:41.791 --> 00:11:45.666
I'm so glad that I ran into you
because I finally got these.

211
00:11:47.625 --> 00:11:48.916
Here.

212
00:11:53.583 --> 00:11:54.833
Wow.

213
00:11:54.916 --> 00:11:57.416
I know how nervous he was about...

214
00:11:58.208 --> 00:11:59.333
just how he looked.

215
00:11:59.416 --> 00:12:02.000
but I kept telling him
that he looked so amazing.

216
00:12:02.083 --> 00:12:04.416
But. I mean. you know. look at him.

217
00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:09.291
Oh. also. he was saying that
you guys went to the beach the other day.

218
00:12:09.375 --> 00:12:13.250
How do I get down there?
Because I would love to set up before

219
00:12:13.333 --> 00:12:15.750
and. you know.
surprise him and everything.

220
00:12:16.666 --> 00:12:17.666
Uh. you just...

221
00:12:18.791 --> 00:12:20.000
Well. you. um...

222
00:12:20.833 --> 00:12:22.000
You just...

223
00:12:23.958 --> 00:12:26.333
The fuck. I guess. Really.

224
00:12:28.458 --> 00:12:30.583
- What?
- The fuck is wrong with you?

225
00:12:31.666 --> 00:12:34.541
What do you think this is.
a fucking country club?

226
00:12:35.208 --> 00:12:36.958
This is a hospice.

227
00:12:37.625 --> 00:12:39.916
Everybody here is really fucking sick.

228
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:41.208
And now you want to. what?

229
00:12:41.833 --> 00:12:44.125
Show him a picture of himself
under 20 pounds of makeup?

230
00:12:44.208 --> 00:12:48.333
I know. I spackled it on for him
just to see how not normal he is.

231
00:12:48.416 --> 00:12:50.333
No. no. no. That's not what I...

232
00:12:50.416 --> 00:12:53.500
Do you understand
what kind of a toll you take on him?

233
00:12:54.833 --> 00:12:57.416
How hard it is for him
to put on a show for you

234
00:12:57.500 --> 00:12:58.750
every fucking time.

235
00:12:59.625 --> 00:13:00.875
He doesn't tell you that

236
00:13:00.958 --> 00:13:03.708
because he doesn't want you to worry
any more than you already do.

237
00:13:03.791 --> 00:13:05.041
And now you want to. what?

238
00:13:05.833 --> 00:13:07.875
Make him walk down to the beach

239
00:13:07.958 --> 00:13:10.500
pretending like
it doesn't hurt like hell for a picnic

240
00:13:10.583 --> 00:13:12.375
so you can feel normal?

241
00:13:13.750 --> 00:13:15.833
He's dying. Katherine.

242
00:13:16.625 --> 00:13:18.416
He's dying and it's not fucking fair.

243
00:13:18.500 --> 00:13:21.500
And that's already hard enough
without having to take care of you

244
00:13:21.583 --> 00:13:23.309
and act all brave
just so you can walk out of here

245
00:13:23.333 --> 00:13:24.666
and live your goddamn life.

246
00:13:24.750 --> 00:13:25.750
Hey!

247
00:13:26.791 --> 00:13:28.125
The fuck are you doing. Ilonka?

248
00:13:49.458 --> 00:13:50.500
What happened?

249
00:13:51.916 --> 00:13:54.333
I need a place to stay.
I can't go back there anymore.

250
00:13:54.916 --> 00:13:56.583
India. make up a bed for Ilonka.

251
00:13:56.666 --> 00:13:59.250
What? What happened?

252
00:14:00.750 --> 00:14:01.958
It's not me.

253
00:14:03.333 --> 00:14:05.541
It's not me. It... it didn't work.

254
00:14:07.041 --> 00:14:09.041
It's not me.

255
00:14:11.583 --> 00:14:13.791
<i>Ilonka lost her goddamn mind.</i>

256
00:14:14.875 --> 00:14:15.875
Yeah.

257
00:14:18.500 --> 00:14:19.500
What?

258
00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:21.916
Ilonka.

259
00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:24.625
- Ilonka what?
- You know "Ilonka what?"

260
00:14:26.416 --> 00:14:27.500
What do you want me to do?

261
00:14:27.583 --> 00:14:29.500
What you want to do.

262
00:14:29.583 --> 00:14:31.708
I'm not breaking up with Katherine.

263
00:14:31.791 --> 00:14:34.291
See? See. I didn't even say it.

264
00:14:34.375 --> 00:14:36.958
I say. do what you want to do.

265
00:14:37.041 --> 00:14:40.583
and you go boom. crash right into
"I'm not breaking up with Katherine."

266
00:14:40.666 --> 00:14:43.750
I've got what? Months left. tops?

267
00:14:44.333 --> 00:14:46.791
And I'm just supposed
to break up with her? Jesus.

268
00:14:47.458 --> 00:14:50.875
Right now.
she's a girl with a sick boyfriend.

269
00:14:51.375 --> 00:14:55.000
and pretty soon.
she'll be a girl with no boyfriend.

270
00:14:55.083 --> 00:14:57.833
So who are you helping by keeping this up?

271
00:14:59.166 --> 00:15:00.526
We both know what you really want.

272
00:15:01.833 --> 00:15:03.333
Who you really want.

273
00:15:04.333 --> 00:15:06.583
You know why I don't finish my stories?

274
00:15:06.666 --> 00:15:07.916
'Cause you're an asshole.

275
00:15:08.833 --> 00:15:10.000
You're a plot tease.

276
00:15:10.083 --> 00:15:12.250
Because once people know the end...

277
00:15:14.166 --> 00:15:16.416
the rest of the story just fades away.

278
00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:21.666
I'm gonna be nothing but a memory soon.

279
00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:26.041
And I would like to be a good one...

280
00:15:27.958 --> 00:15:29.208
for everybody.

281
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:31.541
But for her. especially.

282
00:15:34.416 --> 00:15:35.458
She's earned it.

283
00:15:44.333 --> 00:15:46.000
It's not a lot. but...

284
00:15:46.833 --> 00:15:47.875
it's all we need.

285
00:15:49.416 --> 00:15:51.916
Let's get you some food and some linens.

286
00:15:52.833 --> 00:15:54.083
Thanks for...

287
00:15:55.083 --> 00:15:56.666
I... I don't know what I'm doing.

288
00:15:56.750 --> 00:15:59.041
Maybe a night or two
while I figure it out?

289
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.875
Don't worry about that. Listen.

290
00:16:02.458 --> 00:16:03.625
We need to talk.

291
00:16:03.708 --> 00:16:05.166
I should go back.

292
00:16:05.250 --> 00:16:06.416
Look. Stanton will notice.

293
00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:08.309
and I don't want you
getting in trouble because of me.

294
00:16:08.333 --> 00:16:11.083
I've dealt with more trouble
than Georgina Stanton.

295
00:16:11.166 --> 00:16:12.666
And going back. that's. uh...

296
00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:15.958
That's what I want to talk to you about.

297
00:16:17.083 --> 00:16:19.875
For me. Brightcliffe is special.

298
00:16:20.791 --> 00:16:22.750
- Apparently not.
- Don't.

299
00:16:22.833 --> 00:16:26.833
Don't misinterpret what happened
or didn't happen.

300
00:16:26.916 --> 00:16:29.750
That place is special.

301
00:16:29.833 --> 00:16:32.125
There's a power there and energy there

302
00:16:32.208 --> 00:16:34.291
that doesn't exist
anywhere else in the world.

303
00:16:34.375 --> 00:16:35.375
Believe me.

304
00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:38.125
- I've looked.
- But it didn't work.

305
00:16:39.375 --> 00:16:40.875
- None of it.
- You don't know that.

306
00:16:41.541 --> 00:16:45.208
Maybe it did. maybe it didn't. But it can.

307
00:16:45.833 --> 00:16:47.333
I know that. I know that the...

308
00:16:48.583 --> 00:16:50.833
I know that the ritual works
more than anybody.

309
00:16:53.208 --> 00:16:54.625
Do you hear me? I know it.

310
00:16:56.750 --> 00:16:57.958
Better than anyone.

311
00:16:59.541 --> 00:17:00.750
Who are you?

312
00:17:00.833 --> 00:17:03.041
You're a bright girl. Ilonka.

313
00:17:03.125 --> 00:17:05.750
I've seen it
crossed your mind at least once.

314
00:17:05.833 --> 00:17:07.708
So come on. bright girl.

315
00:17:07.791 --> 00:17:11.250
You look at me. you tell me. who am I?

316
00:17:14.125 --> 00:17:16.666
Take a real look.

317
00:17:20.833 --> 00:17:21.916
You're Julia Jayne?

318
00:17:24.875 --> 00:17:26.458
See. I knew you're a bright girl.

319
00:17:27.750 --> 00:17:29.458
You came looking for me.

320
00:17:29.541 --> 00:17:31.750
You found me because you were right.

321
00:17:34.416 --> 00:17:36.833
You are right about all of it.

322
00:17:44.708 --> 00:17:46.388
Are you going to tell me
where we're going?

323
00:17:46.458 --> 00:17:48.833
Yeah. look. I know it is crazy.

324
00:17:48.916 --> 00:17:52.875
and I know
you've been feeling alone a lot.

325
00:17:54.083 --> 00:17:56.708
Sometimes I forget
you haven't really met people yet.

326
00:17:56.791 --> 00:17:59.166
so I figured you'd want to check this out.

327
00:17:59.958 --> 00:18:01.041
You got a whole community.

328
00:18:02.291 --> 00:18:03.916
It's time you met them. Come on.

329
00:18:09.583 --> 00:18:10.833
- Oh. there he is.
- Hey.

330
00:18:10.916 --> 00:18:12.750
- Hey.
- Hi.

331
00:18:12.833 --> 00:18:14.750
Everybody. this is Spence.

332
00:18:14.833 --> 00:18:16.708
- Hi. Spence.
- Hi. Spence.

333
00:18:16.791 --> 00:18:21.166
Spence. this is everybody.
It's Brandi. Julie. Toni with an "I."

334
00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:23.541
Brian. and Lisa.

335
00:18:23.625 --> 00:18:24.833
What are you all doing?

336
00:18:24.916 --> 00:18:27.500
Waiting for the pizza.
and then it's game night.

337
00:18:27.583 --> 00:18:29.208
Uh. but also...

338
00:18:29.291 --> 00:18:31.875
But also. there's a rally
this weekend at Capitol Hill.

339
00:18:31.958 --> 00:18:33.416
And we're going to represent.

340
00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:36.333
So we're making signs.
helping Glenn with his speech.

341
00:18:36.416 --> 00:18:38.375
Oh. no. You're not going to make a speech.

342
00:18:38.458 --> 00:18:39.875
Uh. of course I am.

343
00:18:39.958 --> 00:18:42.708
Uh. Glenn uses his words
like some people use a billy club.

344
00:18:42.791 --> 00:18:44.875
I know and you know
that I love your sermons.

345
00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:46.916
but this one is just. like.
a little bit clunky.

346
00:18:47.500 --> 00:18:50.833
Oh. I'm sorry.
Is it too clunky for you. Julie?

347
00:18:50.916 --> 00:18:55.375
Our struggle for basic
human recognition is too clunky for you.

348
00:18:55.458 --> 00:18:57.458
Ooh! T-shirts.

349
00:18:57.958 --> 00:18:59.291
Scary T-shirts.

350
00:19:00.333 --> 00:19:02.250
Spence. can I get you a drink or anything?

351
00:19:02.333 --> 00:19:04.333
I'm happy to trade booze
if you want to help.

352
00:19:04.416 --> 00:19:06.875
You want to make some shirts
or some signs.

353
00:19:06.958 --> 00:19:08.250
How can help?

354
00:19:08.333 --> 00:19:09.973
Well. sweetie. grab a paintbrush.

355
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:12.708
And when we're done.
we're gonna get high

356
00:19:12.791 --> 00:19:14.083
and play Catch Phrase.

357
00:19:15.083 --> 00:19:17.041
- Let's do it.
- Hell. yeah.

358
00:19:22.541 --> 00:19:23.916
Do you want any more?

359
00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:26.583
No. no. but that was amazing.

360
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:30.250
It is the best damn food
you will. maybe. ever have.

361
00:19:34.458 --> 00:19:35.750
Why didn't you tell me?

362
00:19:35.833 --> 00:19:38.041
I told you when it was time.

363
00:19:38.833 --> 00:19:40.166
It worked for you.

364
00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:42.916
It works.

365
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:44.041
It does.

366
00:19:45.291 --> 00:19:46.333
I'm proof.

367
00:19:47.583 --> 00:19:49.125
Look. we have much to discuss.

368
00:19:49.208 --> 00:19:51.875
You know about
the most exciting part already.

369
00:19:52.791 --> 00:19:58.833
Uh. after I left. I lived hard and well.

370
00:19:58.916 --> 00:20:04.333
And as I got older.
I... I wanted to share the miracle.

371
00:20:05.333 --> 00:20:06.375
I started Good Humor

372
00:20:06.458 --> 00:20:08.416
because I... I wanted
to understand that better.

373
00:20:08.500 --> 00:20:12.666
I wanted to give back some of that
healing energy into the world.

374
00:20:12.750 --> 00:20:16.416
But it's been difficult
to get back on the property.

375
00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:18.583
The woods are good. the spring is good.

376
00:20:18.666 --> 00:20:20.916
But the magic.
the real magic of this place.

377
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:22.916
it is right where that house is built.

378
00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:25.541
Stanton won't let you back in?

379
00:20:25.625 --> 00:20:28.250
I probably threatened
something fundamentally inside her.

380
00:20:28.333 --> 00:20:30.833
I... I tried everything.
I volunteered at the hospice.

381
00:20:30.916 --> 00:20:33.541
I made donations. generous donations.

382
00:20:33.625 --> 00:20:36.583
But she still won't give us
any meaningful access to the place.

383
00:20:36.666 --> 00:20:38.916
And we are trying
to be respectful of that.

384
00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:41.208
And I understand the history
of the place that...

385
00:20:42.250 --> 00:20:46.166
awful Paragon business.
and collective like mine.

386
00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:51.208
You and I are a lot alike. Ilonka.

387
00:20:52.958 --> 00:20:55.166
You even have the same cancer that I had.

388
00:20:55.250 --> 00:20:56.583
And I don't know. I just...

389
00:20:57.583 --> 00:20:58.666
I want to help you.

390
00:21:01.958 --> 00:21:03.333
You know what? Let's just do it.

391
00:21:04.750 --> 00:21:08.291
I say you and I go back there together
tonight after the Midnight Club.

392
00:21:08.375 --> 00:21:09.583
after everyone's asleep.

393
00:21:09.666 --> 00:21:12.416
you bring me down there
into that basement.

394
00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:15.708
That's where the ley lines intersect.
That's the energy center.

395
00:21:15.791 --> 00:21:18.416
You bring me there.
I have everything that I need.

396
00:21:18.500 --> 00:21:19.875
Everything you need for what?

397
00:21:20.958 --> 00:21:23.666
To heal you. bright girl.

398
00:21:31.291 --> 00:21:32.500
Here you go.

399
00:21:33.416 --> 00:21:35.791
I'm glad you came out tonight.
Hope you had fun.

400
00:21:36.625 --> 00:21:38.083
- Thanks.
- Mm-hm.

401
00:21:38.166 --> 00:21:39.333
That was a blast.

402
00:21:41.250 --> 00:21:42.833
- Can I ask you something?
- Hm?

403
00:21:44.458 --> 00:21:45.708
How'd you get into all that?

404
00:21:46.708 --> 00:21:48.583
Being gay? I was just born that way.

405
00:21:49.250 --> 00:21:51.875
Oh. I'm sorry. You meant Catch Phrase.

406
00:21:52.666 --> 00:21:55.083
That is just an objectively
awesome party game.

407
00:21:55.166 --> 00:21:58.500
No. I mean the activism. I guess.

408
00:22:01.916 --> 00:22:03.833
Dear. dear friend of mine.

409
00:22:05.208 --> 00:22:06.250
But he's gone now.

410
00:22:12.083 --> 00:22:13.083
It was...

411
00:22:14.166 --> 00:22:15.875
I mean. nobody there seems scared...

412
00:22:17.666 --> 00:22:18.875
of anything.

413
00:22:20.791 --> 00:22:22.125
Like. even when I told them...

414
00:22:22.916 --> 00:22:25.041
even when I told them I had AIDS. they...

415
00:22:26.166 --> 00:22:27.583
still didn't seem scared.

416
00:22:30.291 --> 00:22:33.916
Fear's like. it's like radiation.

417
00:22:34.666 --> 00:22:36.833
You spend enough time around enough of it.

418
00:22:36.916 --> 00:22:39.125
and it changes you genetically.

419
00:22:40.500 --> 00:22:42.041
We've lost a lot of us.

420
00:22:42.916 --> 00:22:45.875
Way. way too many of us.

421
00:22:45.958 --> 00:22:48.375
Lot of empty chairs at empty tables.
and the world's...

422
00:22:49.791 --> 00:22:56.125
been indifferent to us at best
and terrified of us at worst.

423
00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:58.666
So a lot of us did a lot of hiding...

424
00:22:59.416 --> 00:23:00.458
for a long time.

425
00:23:02.166 --> 00:23:03.208
That's what I did.

426
00:23:05.666 --> 00:23:06.666
So. now...

427
00:23:08.333 --> 00:23:11.125
more than ever. we need to be visible.

428
00:23:13.208 --> 00:23:14.500
Ryan taught me that.

429
00:23:15.958 --> 00:23:17.000
Taught me a lot.

430
00:23:18.083 --> 00:23:19.208
And that is why we do this.

431
00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:24.041
And that is why
no one there tonight seemed scared.

432
00:23:24.708 --> 00:23:27.333
Because even if we are.
we choose not to be.

433
00:23:28.333 --> 00:23:30.791
Because every single one of us
is going to die someday.

434
00:23:32.166 --> 00:23:35.416
And before we do.
every single one of us deserves love.

435
00:23:47.583 --> 00:23:49.583
I'm so glad she left it open.

436
00:23:49.666 --> 00:23:52.500
Would have been particularly cruel tonight
if the doors were locked.

437
00:23:56.666 --> 00:23:57.791
You okay. Spence?

438
00:23:59.250 --> 00:24:02.333
Hm? Yeah. just...

439
00:24:03.291 --> 00:24:06.375
looking at the chairs. empty chairs.

440
00:24:07.333 --> 00:24:08.791
Almost half of us aren't here.

441
00:24:21.125 --> 00:24:22.125
Hi.

442
00:24:23.125 --> 00:24:26.250
- I wasn't sure if...
- Girl. you better be coming to this table.

443
00:24:26.958 --> 00:24:30.083
Um. I mean. I feel like
everybody's super pissed at me.

444
00:24:31.166 --> 00:24:33.666
Nope. Not even a little.

445
00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:38.083
I am so. so happy for you.

446
00:24:40.166 --> 00:24:42.250
Me too. Come here.

447
00:24:45.125 --> 00:24:48.875
I just needed a minute
to pick my jaw off the floor.

448
00:24:50.833 --> 00:24:52.125
I'm happy for you too.

449
00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:54.750
We love you.

450
00:24:54.833 --> 00:24:56.750
And we love the world with you in it.

451
00:24:56.833 --> 00:24:59.375
So stick around
for as long as you fucking can. got it?

452
00:25:04.125 --> 00:25:06.125
I love you fiercely. darling.

453
00:25:06.208 --> 00:25:08.583
But if you even think
about giving Jesus the credit.

454
00:25:08.666 --> 00:25:12.250
I'mma haunt you twice as scary
because I'm going to definitely haunt you

455
00:25:12.333 --> 00:25:14.583
after that intercom nonsense.
you got it coming.

456
00:25:15.166 --> 00:25:16.916
Not my finest hour.

457
00:25:27.541 --> 00:25:28.583
Hi.

458
00:25:31.875 --> 00:25:33.000
I'm. um...

459
00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:35.833
I'm really sorry.

460
00:25:37.041 --> 00:25:38.958
I'm sorry. Sandra. and...

461
00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:41.416
And I'm sorry. Kevin.

462
00:25:42.291 --> 00:25:43.791
I'm just really sorry.

463
00:25:44.833 --> 00:25:47.041
I'm really happy you're here.

464
00:25:50.666 --> 00:25:51.791
I'm happy too.

465
00:25:53.041 --> 00:25:54.041
For you.

466
00:26:03.666 --> 00:26:06.833
Sit. please. I'm going tonight.

467
00:26:06.916 --> 00:26:09.416
And. well. this one's from the heart.

468
00:26:12.458 --> 00:26:15.166
To those before. and to those after.

469
00:26:16.083 --> 00:26:18.666
To us now. and to those beyond.

470
00:26:18.750 --> 00:26:21.750
To those before. to those after.

471
00:26:21.833 --> 00:26:24.250
To us now. and to those beyond.

472
00:26:24.333 --> 00:26:28.125
Seen or unseen. here but not here.

473
00:26:28.208 --> 00:26:31.375
Seen or unseen. here but not here.

474
00:26:32.166 --> 00:26:36.708
Oh. the story I want to tell
actually scares the shit out of me.

475
00:26:36.791 --> 00:26:40.583
It's a story about knowing
where you're going before you get there.

476
00:26:40.666 --> 00:26:44.583
It's a story about fighting
for the future that you want

477
00:26:44.666 --> 00:26:46.708
instead of the future
that you're destined for.

478
00:26:46.791 --> 00:26:49.458
because destinies can change.

479
00:26:50.000 --> 00:26:51.958
I think we all figured that out today.

480
00:26:53.750 --> 00:26:55.041
I call this one...

481
00:26:56.083 --> 00:26:58.500
"The Eternal Enemy."

482
00:27:00.208 --> 00:27:03.750
<i>This is a story
about time and fear.</i>

483
00:27:03.833 --> 00:27:07.083
<i>Time has a permanent hold on us
the moment we're born.</i>

484
00:27:07.166 --> 00:27:09.916
<i>It allows us to grow. to get big.</i>

485
00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:12.958
<i>We go to school. we find jobs.
we fall in love.</i>

486
00:27:13.041 --> 00:27:17.875
<i>Time lets us do all of these things.
But then. in the end. it kills us.</i>

487
00:27:18.791 --> 00:27:20.166
<i>This is Rel.</i>

488
00:27:20.250 --> 00:27:22.500
<i>He's devilishly handsome.
wildly attractive.</i>

489
00:27:22.583 --> 00:27:24.666
<i>Hard to believe
he's not a model. actually.</i>

490
00:27:24.750 --> 00:27:25.875
<i>We get it.</i>

491
00:27:25.958 --> 00:27:29.833
<i>Despite his obvious appeal.
he doesn't have a ton of friends.</i>

492
00:27:38.125 --> 00:27:39.666
<i>Rel's a transfer student.</i>

493
00:27:39.750 --> 00:27:42.125
<i>new to town. only on campus three weeks.</i>

494
00:27:42.208 --> 00:27:44.916
<i>but there's someone
he really wants to know better.</i>

495
00:27:45.541 --> 00:27:48.583
<i>Christopher Perry. resident genius.</i>

496
00:27:49.250 --> 00:27:51.083
<i>In fact. every day since he got here.</i>

497
00:27:51.166 --> 00:27:53.708
<i>Christopher has been the only person
Rel could think about.</i>

498
00:27:55.041 --> 00:27:56.458
The whole board is fried.

499
00:27:57.125 --> 00:27:59.083
You can't fix it?
I thought you can fix anything.

500
00:27:59.166 --> 00:28:02.625
I'm afraid I got no cure for the bubblegum
you Neanderthals got into the gears.

501
00:28:02.708 --> 00:28:05.108
I mean. like.
how the hell do you even do that?

502
00:28:07.250 --> 00:28:09.291
<i>It was lonely enough
being the new guy.</i>

503
00:28:09.833 --> 00:28:11.166
<i>Even worse without a roommate</i>

504
00:28:11.250 --> 00:28:14.250
<i>and that's what he told himself
when he bought the VCR.</i>

505
00:28:15.583 --> 00:28:18.000
<i>He could set it up
