747
00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:21.125
You got to see this.

748
00:41:21.208 --> 00:41:23.288
- We said you wouldn't.
- You got to get out of here.

749
00:41:23.750 --> 00:41:25.083
If anything happened to you...

750
00:41:35.500 --> 00:41:36.500
Chris?

751
00:41:37.958 --> 00:41:39.458
What on earth is going on here?

752
00:41:44.166 --> 00:41:46.291
No. no. no. no...

753
00:42:57.875 --> 00:42:58.934
Who the fuck are you?

754
00:42:58.958 --> 00:43:01.250
And why are you trying
to kill Christopher?

755
00:43:02.416 --> 00:43:04.250
And why do you look like Christopher?

756
00:43:04.333 --> 00:43:05.666
I'm not trying to kill him.

757
00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:08.250
You are.

758
00:43:08.333 --> 00:43:11.000
- What the fuck does that mean?
- You're trying to kill him.

759
00:43:11.083 --> 00:43:12.583
You're trying to kill all of us.

760
00:43:13.750 --> 00:43:16.291
You really think
you're just a normal college student?

761
00:43:16.875 --> 00:43:18.041
Let me ask you this.

762
00:43:19.166 --> 00:43:20.446
Where did you go to high school?

763
00:43:21.500 --> 00:43:24.333
Where were you born? Where's your family?

764
00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:27.875
You don't remember?
Because you weren't a person.

765
00:43:28.583 --> 00:43:29.666
You weren't born.

766
00:43:30.916 --> 00:43:32.041
You were made.

767
00:43:34.041 --> 00:43:34.875
In a lab.

768
00:43:34.958 --> 00:43:37.083
My lab. 40 years from now.

769
00:43:37.166 --> 00:43:40.708
My lab
in Robotic Experimentation Logistics.

770
00:43:43.250 --> 00:43:44.333
R.E.L.

771
00:43:45.000 --> 00:43:46.583
You kept that for a name.

772
00:43:47.333 --> 00:43:48.750
You're a cyborg.

773
00:43:50.166 --> 00:43:51.250
An early model.

774
00:43:52.458 --> 00:43:53.833
And you're defective.

775
00:43:54.500 --> 00:43:56.833
I was going to terminate you.
But you escaped.

776
00:43:57.416 --> 00:43:59.291
You escaped back in time.

777
00:43:59.375 --> 00:44:01.166
What kind of bullshit is this?

778
00:44:01.250 --> 00:44:02.583
Look at your hand.

779
00:44:04.125 --> 00:44:05.833
No. take... take a good look.

780
00:44:29.791 --> 00:44:32.916
No. Liar. Liar.

781
00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:35.250
You fucking liar.

782
00:44:44.291 --> 00:44:45.875
What the fuck?

783
00:44:45.958 --> 00:44:47.000
Yep.

784
00:44:47.666 --> 00:44:48.750
Me too.

785
00:44:50.375 --> 00:44:51.541
I'm the first.

786
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.458
I was him once. But. uh...

787
00:44:58.125 --> 00:44:59.125
I got sick.

788
00:44:59.958 --> 00:45:03.625
And I replaced this part.
and that part. and this part.

789
00:45:04.458 --> 00:45:06.833
And before long. I was more than human.

790
00:45:07.666 --> 00:45:09.750
I was the first of a new species.

791
00:45:09.833 --> 00:45:11.083
And I made more.

792
00:45:11.916 --> 00:45:13.000
I made you.

793
00:45:13.708 --> 00:45:15.500
You were one of my earliest models.

794
00:45:15.583 --> 00:45:17.250
You said I was defective.

795
00:45:17.333 --> 00:45:18.750
You suffer from a disease.

796
00:45:19.458 --> 00:45:21.625
A disease called fear.

797
00:45:22.458 --> 00:45:23.500
Sadness.

798
00:45:24.083 --> 00:45:26.708
I've removed those in the future.
We've. uh...

799
00:45:27.875 --> 00:45:30.125
We've cured them. I've cured them.

800
00:45:30.708 --> 00:45:32.750
But you. you escaped.

801
00:45:33.458 --> 00:45:35.708
And when you saved that woman.

802
00:45:36.291 --> 00:45:37.958
you let yourself be photographed.

803
00:45:39.500 --> 00:45:40.625
And I found you...

804
00:45:42.666 --> 00:45:43.666
back in time.

805
00:45:45.125 --> 00:45:46.416
I don't remember.

806
00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:49.708
You wouldn't.
Time travel is different for your model.

807
00:45:49.791 --> 00:45:51.833
And your memory gets damaged
in the process.

808
00:45:51.916 --> 00:45:53.583
There's no way you could have known that.

809
00:45:53.666 --> 00:45:55.583
But I built in a background code.

810
00:45:56.416 --> 00:45:58.041
Programmed to print on whatever it can

811
00:45:58.125 --> 00:46:00.005
to remind you
of whatever your mission might be.

812
00:46:00.500 --> 00:46:01.916
And it did.

813
00:46:02.000 --> 00:46:05.375
Every time you touch
one of those primitive magnetic devices.

814
00:46:06.375 --> 00:46:07.500
It wasn't the VCR.

815
00:46:07.583 --> 00:46:11.666
It was you. your mainframe.
trying to remind you of your mission.

816
00:46:12.250 --> 00:46:15.583
You came here to kill me.
to stop the future from happening.

817
00:46:15.666 --> 00:46:18.208
To stop me creating what I must create.

818
00:46:18.291 --> 00:46:19.500
But I came to stop you.

819
00:46:20.625 --> 00:46:22.208
To save us all.

820
00:46:23.458 --> 00:46:26.041
And when you found me.
you knew you needed to be close to me.

821
00:46:27.083 --> 00:46:28.666
But you'd forgotten why.

822
00:46:29.958 --> 00:46:31.166
But you attacked us.

823
00:46:31.666 --> 00:46:35.083
I used anesthetic gas.
that only affects humans. They'll be fine.

824
00:46:35.166 --> 00:46:37.041
And when they wake up. you'll be gone.

825
00:46:37.916 --> 00:46:39.750
It'll all feel like a dream.

826
00:46:40.666 --> 00:46:42.541
This is where you end. Rel.

827
00:46:43.416 --> 00:46:46.291
Why? I'm not defective.

828
00:46:46.375 --> 00:46:50.625
You still feel the eternal problem.
the eternal enemy lives in you.

829
00:46:51.333 --> 00:46:52.375
Fear.

830
00:46:52.458 --> 00:46:53.666
Which leads to suffering.

831
00:46:54.166 --> 00:46:57.916
And we deserve to live
in a world without fear. Rel.

832
00:46:58.000 --> 00:46:59.375
Without suffering.

833
00:47:03.916 --> 00:47:05.250
You're moving again.

834
00:47:05.833 --> 00:47:10.458
That current paralyzed me briefly.
but it was never going to stop me.

835
00:47:11.333 --> 00:47:15.208
Replacing humanity
with these cybernetic improvements.

836
00:47:15.291 --> 00:47:17.125
Rooting out defects.

837
00:47:17.208 --> 00:47:18.875
Isn't all of that just fear?

838
00:47:19.833 --> 00:47:21.000
It is. isn't it?

839
00:47:21.958 --> 00:47:25.333
If you need me to die
so you'll feel a little less afraid...

840
00:47:27.250 --> 00:47:28.291
whatever.

841
00:47:29.583 --> 00:47:30.666
You do you.

842
00:47:32.041 --> 00:47:33.583
But I'm not defective.

843
00:47:34.708 --> 00:47:35.791
You are.

844
00:47:37.958 --> 00:47:39.250
And I love you anyway.

845
00:48:26.041 --> 00:48:27.625
<i>Hi. sweetie.</i>

846
00:48:27.708 --> 00:48:29.375
<i>I'm uploading this in a split sec.</i>

847
00:48:29.458 --> 00:48:32.000
<i>I don't have much time
because you're about to kill me.</i>

848
00:48:32.083 --> 00:48:34.916
<i>which is okay. don't worry about that.</i>

849
00:48:35.000 --> 00:48:38.083
<i>But I want you to know the truth
about who I am.</i>

850
00:48:38.166 --> 00:48:40.875
<i>about what you're going to become. and...</i>

851
00:48:41.958 --> 00:48:46.250
<i>about the things your brilliant brain
is going to do to this world.</i>

852
00:48:48.500 --> 00:48:49.916
<i>And he saw it all.</i>

853
00:48:50.000 --> 00:48:52.166
<i>All the great and terrible things he'd do.</i>

854
00:48:52.250 --> 00:48:55.750
<i>all the amazing technological
accomplishments he'd make</i>

855
00:48:55.833 --> 00:48:59.333
<i>in his effort to eliminate suffering.
to eliminate fear.</i>

856
00:49:00.083 --> 00:49:03.791
<i>And in doing so.
he saw how he'd lose his humanity.</i>

857
00:49:05.708 --> 00:49:06.708
<i>So that's it.</i>

858
00:49:07.708 --> 00:49:09.000
<i>I wanted you to know...</i>

859
00:49:10.333 --> 00:49:14.250
<i>when I think of that.
of what you become. I feel sad.</i>

860
00:49:15.416 --> 00:49:16.666
<i>Very sad. but...</i>

861
00:49:18.041 --> 00:49:19.458
<i>there's beauty in sorrow.</i>

862
00:49:20.625 --> 00:49:21.750
<i>I realize that now.</i>

863
00:49:22.958 --> 00:49:24.166
<i>How fragile we are.</i>

864
00:49:25.291 --> 00:49:27.833
<i>I'm afraid I don't have time
to tell you any more</i>

865
00:49:28.625 --> 00:49:31.000
<i>because my old friend
has come for me. and...</i>

866
00:49:31.791 --> 00:49:32.833
<i>that's okay.</i>

867
00:49:34.291 --> 00:49:35.458
<i>Because I loved.</i>

868
00:49:37.291 --> 00:49:38.458
<i>Because I loved.</i>

869
00:49:40.208 --> 00:49:41.208
<i>Thank you.</i>

870
00:49:42.166 --> 00:49:43.083
<i>Thank you. Christopher.</i>

871
00:49:45.833 --> 00:49:49.125
<i>And in that moment.
the future changed.</i>

872
00:49:49.791 --> 00:49:52.416
<i>because Christopher decided</i>

873
00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:56.916
<i>that he'd never. ever look at his fellow
human beings and see defects.</i>

874
00:49:57.000 --> 00:50:00.125
<i>He'd look at them
through the eyes of love.</i>

875
00:50:01.291 --> 00:50:03.833
<i>because Rel wasn't defective at all.
it turns out.</i>

876
00:50:04.791 --> 00:50:06.041
<i>Rel was perfect.</i>

877
00:50:18.750 --> 00:50:21.791
You once told me about your friend.

878
00:50:22.750 --> 00:50:25.458
- The one who...
- Got me sick. Yeah.

879
00:50:26.250 --> 00:50:27.250
Christopher.

880
00:50:27.958 --> 00:50:29.375
And I think about him a lot.

881
00:50:30.833 --> 00:50:32.166
But I hope he's loved.

882
00:50:33.791 --> 00:50:34.875
Like I'm loved.

883
00:50:36.666 --> 00:50:38.750
I wish we knew back then what I know now.

884
00:50:40.416 --> 00:50:41.666
We weren't defective.

885
00:50:42.541 --> 00:50:43.666
Not even a little bit.

886
00:50:46.625 --> 00:50:47.833
We were perfect.

887
00:50:48.833 --> 00:50:50.000
Just like all of you.

888
00:50:51.083 --> 00:50:53.416
And. um. Sandra.

889
00:50:54.541 --> 00:50:56.791
you go make that future
something good. okay?

890
00:50:58.000 --> 00:50:59.000
For us.

891
00:51:30.541 --> 00:51:32.208
What... Who are...

892
00:51:32.291 --> 00:51:34.875
It's five sisters.
We need all five. Don't worry.

893
00:51:34.958 --> 00:51:36.918
You didn't tell me
you were bringing other people.

894
00:51:37.000 --> 00:51:38.166
Where's the nurse?

895
00:51:39.083 --> 00:51:40.250
She went to the bathroom.

896
00:51:40.333 --> 00:51:42.093
That's why I was late.
I had to wait for her.

897
00:51:42.666 --> 00:51:44.916
- She'll be back any minute.
- Let's go.

898
00:51:59.666 --> 00:52:00.666
My God.

899
00:52:01.500 --> 00:52:02.666
Do you feel it?

900
00:52:03.500 --> 00:52:05.791
Do you feel it here? It's still here.

901
00:52:07.208 --> 00:52:09.458
It's in the air.
Do you feel it. bright girl?

902
00:52:10.875 --> 00:52:13.000
So what do we do? What do we...

903
00:52:13.083 --> 00:52:14.250
We know what to do.

904
00:52:14.333 --> 00:52:17.666
We'll form four points
with one in the center.

905
00:52:20.291 --> 00:52:21.491
- Here?
- No.

906
00:52:22.000 --> 00:52:24.208
Dear. you sit there.

907
00:53:04.041 --> 00:53:05.375
I don't understand.

908
00:53:05.458 --> 00:53:07.208
You'll see. dear.

909
00:53:08.166 --> 00:53:09.208
Trust me.

910
00:53:12.500 --> 00:53:13.916
- Aceso.
- Aceso.

911
00:53:14.000 --> 00:53:16.083
- Aegle.
- Aegle.

912
00:53:16.166 --> 00:53:19.125
We call on you. the five sisters.

913
00:53:19.208 --> 00:53:23.916
Daughters of Asclepius and Epione.
purveyor of Apollo's arts.

914
00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:28.708
We call on you
to heal your sister. your vessel.

915
00:53:51.208 --> 00:53:57.000
Panacea. Hygeia.
Iaso. Aceso. Aegle.

916
00:53:58.000 --> 00:54:03.291
Panacea. Hygeia. Iaso. Aceso. Aegle.

917
00:54:03.875 --> 00:54:08.791
Kind Panacea.
daughter of Asclepius and Epione.

918
00:54:08.875 --> 00:54:12.583
first of physicians. swiftest of healers.

919
00:54:12.666 --> 00:54:15.541
trusted mender of men and women.

920
00:54:15.625 --> 00:54:21.333
Through you. our wounds healed.
bones knit. and illness burnt away.

921
00:54:33.500 --> 00:54:34.500
Here.

922
00:54:49.416 --> 00:54:51.166
What about our personal items?

923
00:54:52.666 --> 00:54:56.583
By your goodness and might.
we regain joy in our lives.

924
00:54:56.666 --> 00:54:59.083
Panacea. friend to mankind.

925
00:54:59.166 --> 00:55:02.041
We pray to you. I seek your favor.

926
00:55:02.791 --> 00:55:06.083
Let your true believer
be healed of this affliction.

927
00:55:06.166 --> 00:55:09.041
May she recover through and through.

928
00:55:09.125 --> 00:55:12.416
May vigor and vitality return to her.

929
00:55:12.500 --> 00:55:14.958
We ask your blessing.

930
00:55:19.000 --> 00:55:20.708
Our goddess. for you.

931
00:55:21.333 --> 00:55:22.973
- But what about our sacrifice?
- We'll...

932
00:55:23.000 --> 00:55:25.125
We'll get there. This is different.

933
00:55:31.625 --> 00:55:32.708
What's in this?

934
00:55:33.458 --> 00:55:34.500
It's just tea.

935
00:55:35.291 --> 00:55:36.291
Drink it.

936
00:55:40.625 --> 00:55:42.916
Our goddess. for you.

937
00:55:48.500 --> 00:55:49.541
Go on.

938
00:55:52.125 --> 00:55:53.166
Go ahead.

939
00:55:55.500 --> 00:55:56.559
Hello. Julia.

940
00:56:04.083 --> 00:56:05.500
Drink it. Drink it now!

941
00:56:05.583 --> 00:56:07.333
No! Ilonka. do not drink that!

942
00:56:07.416 --> 00:56:09.583
Drink it now. It has to be now or never.

943
00:56:09.666 --> 00:56:11.726
- It will not work if you don't drink it.
- No!

944
00:56:11.750 --> 00:56:14.083
- Don't!
- Please. Ilonka. Please!

945
00:56:14.166 --> 00:56:15.166
No!

